## 🔀 Page Interactions & Navigation (href)

Every clickable element that navigates to another page **must preserve its `href` link** in HTML and must be represented as a Figma prototype interaction.

### HTML Rule

All navigation links must use real anchor tags:

```html
<!-- Correct -->
<a href="lobby-hub.html" class="BottomNav__Item">Lobby</a>
<button class="LobbyCard__JoinButton" onclick="location.href='session-lobby.html'">Join</button>

<!-- Wrong — no navigation -->
<div class="BottomNav__Item">Lobby</div>
```

### Figma Prototype Rule

When implementing in Figma:

* Every button, nav item, or card that links to another page must have a **Prototype interaction** set:
  * Trigger: `On Click`
  * Action: `Navigate To`
  * Destination: the corresponding Figma frame for that page
* Use the **same page names** as the HTML filenames (e.g., `lobby-hub`, `session-lobby`, `profile`)
* All bottom navigation items must be linked across every screen they appear on

### Page Interaction Map

