## 🚫 Layers to Ignore

The following layers must be excluded from MCP output:

* `Body`
* `Container`
* Any generic wrapper frames that do not represent UI components

> These layers are considered structural noise and should not be translated into HTML.

---

## ✅ Required Root Level

* Always start from: `Section`
* Treat `Section` as the **root container**

Example:

```
Body
 └ Section
    └ Container
       ├ Navigation
       ├ Header
       └ Section
```

### ✅ Expected Output Structure

```
Section (root)
 ├ Navigation
 ├ Header
 └ Section
```

---

## 🧱 HTML Mapping Rule

* The extracted `Section` must be mapped as the main container:

```html
<div class="phone">
  <!-- children from Section -->
</div>
```

* Do NOT recreate `Body` or `Container` in HTML

---

## 🧾 Standard MCP Prompt Template

Use this prompt for consistent results:

```txt
Get design context for the Section node only.

Rules:
- Ignore Body, Container, and any outer wrapper layers
- Treat Section as the root container
- Output only direct children inside Section
- Do not recreate unnecessary wrapper divs
- Keep structure flat and component-based
- Use localhost asset URLs directly — no placeholders
- Preserve all href links as Figma prototype interactions (On Click → Navigate To)
- Apply Auto Layout to all frames — no manual positioning
- Enable vertical scroll on pages with content exceeding 844px height
```

---

## ⚡ Advanced Control (Optional)

If MCP still returns unwanted layers:

```txt
Flatten the hierarchy starting from Section.

Remove all non-essential wrapper layers (Body, Container)
and simplify into clean UI components only.
```

---

## 🧩 Component Expectations

Each child inside `Section` must:

* Represent a real UI block (e.g., `Navigation`, `Header`, `CardList`)
* Be reusable
* Have semantic naming
* Avoid generic names like `div1`, `group`, `frame`

---

## 🚫 What NOT to Do

* Do not include:

  * `Body`
  * `Container`
  * Empty wrapper divs
* Do not nest unnecessarily
* Do not recreate full Figma hierarchy
* Do not skip `get_screenshot` — visual validation is required
* Do not use placeholders when MCP provides a localhost asset URL
* Do not add new icon packages — use only what MCP provides

---

## ✅ Expected Outcome

### ❌ Bad Output

```html
<div class="Body">
  <div class="Container">
    <div class="Section">
      ...
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
```

### ✅ Good Output

```html
<div class="phone">
  <nav class="Navigation"></nav>
  <header class="Header"></header>
  <section class="MainSection"></section>
</div>
```

---

## 🏁 Final Rules

> If a layer does not represent a real UI component, **remove it.**

> If MCP provides a localhost asset URL, **use it directly — never substitute a placeholder.**

> Always call `get_screenshot` and validate visually before marking any task complete.

> Every clickable element that navigates to another page **must have a Figma prototype interaction** wired up — no dead buttons.

> All frames must use **Auto Layout** — never manual positioning.

> Pages with long content **must have vertical scroll enabled** in Figma with `Clip content: ON` and a hugging inner frame.
